Doc,<br><br>
There have been insults on this site to last a lifetime and they probably will.  You ask for the freedom to post on a site without a single entry of anyone who does not agree with you.  This is a luxury that you also have not afforded anyone.<br><br>
Let's not be hypocrites.  If we want to insult then lets do it an articulate manner and leave out the base language.  It includes all the lies like the ones you posted on Cook.  You had the wrong guy.  Nobody needs this type of behavior.  Not you or I or this site or any of my BOCs.<br><br>
If you want an exclusive thread then identify it for War Protestor comment.  I will read, but not comment unless it threatens the site.  Post, but do not defile your nation with words, which once spoken cannot be retracted.  Anger causes such at least I hope it is anger.<br><br>
We have talked of history and the wisdom that it has contained.  Think upon this:<br><br>
&quot;There is one source, O Athenians, of all <br>
your defeats.  It is that your citizens <br>
have ceased to be soldiers.<br><br>
Demosthenes, 383-322 B. C.<br><br>
Nations whose citizens cease to be soldiers are destined to fall.  I feel no man can either not be a soldier in spirit or support them in some manner and not be a participant in the decline of that which he enjoys.<br><br>
PS.  I would assure you would never want to call out ED.  To even think about it tells me you do not have any idea who he is.  He is bigger than life and his words.  A highly respected hero even in the ranks of the most current battle groups.  Evidenced by his speech at FT. Hood the largest of its kind.  Current Army Brass read this site including some West Pointers.  He has earned his place in history, the rest of us are still trying.<br>

